msgid "# Fine-Grained Tensor Parallelism (Fine-grained TP)"
msgstr "# 细粒度张量并行"

msgid "## Overview"
msgstr "## 概述"

msgid ""
"Fine-Grained Tensor Parallelism (Fine-grained TP) extends standard tensor "
"parallelism by enabling **independent tensor-parallel sizes for different "
"model components**. Instead of applying a single global "
"`tensor_parallel_size` to all layers, Fine-grained TP allows users to "
"configure separate TP sizes for key modules—such as embedding, language "
"model head (lm_head), attention output projection (o_proj), and MLP "
"blocks—via the `finegrained_tp_config` parameter."
msgstr ""
"细粒度张量并行通过允许为不同模型组件设置**独立的张量并行大小**，扩展了标准张量并行。细粒度 TP 并非对所有层应用单一的全局 "
"`tensor_parallel_size`，而是允许用户通过 `finegrained_tp_config` 参数为关键模块（如嵌入层、语言模型头 "
"(lm_head)、注意力输出投影 (o_proj) 和 MLP 块）配置独立的 TP 大小。"

msgid ""
"This capability supports heterogeneous parallelism strategies within a "
"single model, providing finer control over weight distribution, memory "
"layout, and communication patterns across devices. The feature is compatible"
" with standard dense transformer architectures and integrates seamlessly "
"into vLLM’s serving pipeline."
msgstr ""
"此功能支持在单个模型内采用异构并行策略，从而对跨设备的权重分布、内存布局和通信模式提供更精细的控制。该特性与标准稠密 Transformer "
"架构兼容，并能无缝集成到 vLLM 的服务流程中。"

msgid "## Supported Scenarios"
msgstr "## 支持场景"

msgid "### Models"
msgstr "### 模型"

msgid ""
"Fine-grained TP is **model-agnostic** and supports all standard dense "
"transformer architectures, including Llama, Qwen, DeepSeek (base/dense "
"variants), and others."
msgstr ""
"细粒度 TP 是**模型无关的**，支持所有标准稠密 Transformer 架构，包括 Llama、Qwen、DeepSeek（基础/稠密变体）等。"

msgid "### Component & Execution Mode Support"
msgstr "### 组件与执行模式支持"

msgid ""
"| TP config     | Eager | Graph | Hybrid | Prefill | Decode |\n"
"| ------------- | ----- | ----- | ------ | ------- | ------ |\n"
"| **embedding** | ✅     | ✅     | ✅      | ✅       | ✅      |\n"
"| **o_proj**    | ❌     | ✅     | ❌      | ❌       | ✅      |\n"
"| **mlp**       | ✅     | ✅     | ✅      | ✅       | ✅      |\n"
"| **LMhead**    | ✅     | ✅     | ✅      | ✅       | ✅      |"
msgstr ""
"| TP 配置       | Eager | Graph | Hybrid | Prefill | Decode |\n"
"| ------------- | ----- | ----- | ------ | ------- | ------ |\n"
"| **embedding** | ✅     | ✅     | ✅      | ✅       | ✅      |\n"
"| **o_proj**    | ❌     | ✅     | ❌      | ❌       | ✅      |\n"
"| **mlp**       | ✅     | ✅     | ✅      | ✅       | ✅      |\n"
"| **LMhead**    | ✅     | ✅     | ✅      | ✅       | ✅      |"

msgid ""
"> ⚠️ Note:  \n"
">\n"
"> - `o_proj` TP is only supported in Graph mode during Decode, because dummy_run in eager mode will not trigger o_proj.\n"
"> - `mlp` TP supports dense models, or dense layers in MoE models. For example, the first three dense layers of DeepSeek-R1."
msgstr ""
"> ⚠️ 注意：  \n"
">\n"
"> - `o_proj` TP 仅在 Decode 阶段的 Graph 模式下支持，因为 eager 模式下的 dummy_run 不会触发 o_proj。\n"
"> - `mlp` TP 支持稠密模型，或 MoE 模型中的稠密层。例如，DeepSeek-R1 的前三个稠密层。"

msgid "### Configuration Limit"
msgstr "### 配置限制"

msgid "The Fine-Grained TP size for any component must:"
msgstr "任何组件的细粒度 TP 大小必须满足："

msgid ""
"- Be **≤ the data-parallel (DP) size**, and  \n"
"- **Evenly divide the DP size** (i.e., `dp_size % tp_size == 0`) to ensure valid device assignment and communication grouping."
msgstr ""
"- **≤ 数据并行 (DP) 大小**，并且  \n"
"- **能整除 DP 大小**（即 `dp_size % tp_size == 0`），以确保有效的设备分配和通信分组。"

msgid ""
"> ⚠️ Violating these constraints will result in runtime errors or undefined "
"behavior."
msgstr "> ⚠️ 违反这些约束将导致运行时错误或未定义行为。"

msgid "## How to Use Fine-grained TP"
msgstr "## 如何使用细粒度 TP"

msgid "### Configuration Format"
msgstr "### 配置格式"

msgid ""
"Fine-grained TP is controlled via the `finegrained_tp_config` field inside "
"`--additional-config`."
msgstr "细粒度 TP 通过 `--additional-config` 中的 `finegrained_tp_config` 字段进行控制。"

msgid "### Example Usage"
msgstr "### 使用示例"

msgid "## Experimental Results"
msgstr "## 实验结果"

msgid ""
"To evaluate the effectiveness of fine-grained TP in large-scale service "
"scenarios, we use the model **DeepSeek-R1-W8A8**, deploy PD separated decode"
" instances in an environment of 32 cards Ascend Atlas A2 inference "
"products*64G (A2), with parallel configuration as DP32+EP32, and fine-"
"grained TP size of 8; the performance data is as follows."
msgstr ""
"为了评估细粒度 TP 在大规模服务场景中的有效性，我们使用 **DeepSeek-R1-W8A8** 模型，在 32 卡 Ascend Atlas A2"
" 推理产品*64G (A2) 环境中部署 PD 分离的 decode 实例，并行配置为 DP32+EP32，细粒度 TP 大小为 8；性能数据如下。"

msgid ""
"| Module           | Memory Savings | TPOT Impact (batch=24)    |\n"
"| ---------------- | -------------- | ------------------------- |\n"
"| o_proj TP = 8    | 5.8 GB         | **+1.5 ms** (degradation) |\n"
"| LM head TP = 8   | 1.51 GB        | **−1.2 ms** (improvement) |\n"
"|  FFN TP = 8 | 0.9 GB         | **−1.0 ms** (improvement) |\n"
"| Embedding TP = 8 | 1.51 GB        | **−1.0 ms** (improvement) |\n"
"| **Total**        | **9.72 GB**    | —                         |"
msgstr ""
"| 模块             | 内存节省       | TPOT 影响 (batch=24)      |\n"
"| ---------------- | -------------- | ------------------------- |\n"
"| o_proj TP = 8    | 5.8 GB         | **+1.5 ms** (性能下降)    |\n"
"| LM head TP = 8   | 1.51 GB        | **−1.2 ms** (性能提升)    |\n"
"|  FFN TP = 8 | 0.9 GB         | **−1.0 ms** (性能提升)    |\n"
"| Embedding TP = 8 | 1.51 GB        | **−1.0 ms** (性能提升)    |\n"
"| **总计**         | **9.72 GB**    | —                         |"

msgid ""
"- We achieved significant gains in terms of high memory capacity on a single"
" card, as well as the benefits of TPOT."
msgstr "- 我们在单卡高内存容量以及 TPOT 收益方面取得了显著成果。"

msgid "## ✅ Deployment Recommendations"
msgstr "## ✅ 部署建议"

msgid ""
"Fine-grained TP is the **most effective** in the **decode instance** of PD "
"separation, where models are typically deployed in all-DP mode. In this "
"setup, sharding weight-heavy layers reduces redundant storage and memory "
"pressure."
msgstr ""
"细粒度 TP 在 PD 分离的 **decode 实例**中**最为有效**，因为模型通常以全 DP "
"模式部署。在此设置下，对权重较大的层进行分片可以减少冗余存储和内存压力。"

msgid "## Benefits of Fine-grained TP"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fine-Grained Tensor Parallelism delivers two primary performance advantages "
"through targeted weight sharding:"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"- **Reduced Per-Device Memory Footprint**:  \n"
"  Fine-grained TP shards large weight matrices (e.g., LM Head, o_proj) across devices, lowering peak memory usage and enabling larger batches or deployment on memory-limited hardware—without quantization."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"- **Faster Memory Access in GEMMs**:  \n"
"  In decode-heavy workloads, GEMM performance is often memory-bound. Weight sharding reduces per-device weight fetch volume, cutting DRAM traffic and improving bandwidth efficiency—especially for latency-sensitive layers like LM Head and o_proj."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Together, these effects allow practitioners to better balance memory, "
"communication, and compute—particularly in high-concurrency serving "
"scenarios—while maintaining compatibility with standard dense transformer "
"models."
msgstr ""
